WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.494 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.494 --> 00:00:59.310 align:middle line:90%


00:00:59.310 --> 00:01:03.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Three, two, one, and you
can look right into the camera.

00:01:03.850 --> 00:01:05.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Greetings, everyone.

00:01:05.610 --> 00:01:08.340 align:middle line:84%
This is Barbara Marx
Hubbard, and I'm in Byron--

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:11.370 align:middle line:84%
(VOICEOVER) This is how
most people know me.

00:01:11.370 --> 00:01:14.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm a speaker and writer.

00:01:14.310 --> 00:01:17.160 align:middle line:84%
But more importantly,
I'm a teacher,

00:01:17.160 --> 00:01:21.180 align:middle line:84%
always reaching out to my
students wherever they are.

00:01:21.180 --> 00:01:24.540 align:middle line:84%
I teach teleseminars
and live workshops.

00:01:24.540 --> 00:01:25.980 align:middle line:90%
I lecture.

00:01:25.980 --> 00:01:27.660 align:middle line:90%
I make films.

00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:31.180 align:middle line:84%
I believe I have a very
important message for the world

00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:31.980 align:middle line:90%
to hear.

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:33.390 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTER]

00:01:33.390 --> 00:01:37.740 align:middle line:84%
Our world is ripe for
change, and our future

00:01:37.740 --> 00:01:44.010 align:middle line:84%
can be astonishing if
we choose to make it so.

00:01:44.010 --> 00:01:48.510 align:middle line:84%
For decades, I've
made my life purpose

00:01:48.510 --> 00:01:52.470 align:middle line:84%
the evolution of our
species through co-creation.

00:01:52.470 --> 00:01:56.430 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my own path, I
started out in Washington DC

00:01:56.430 --> 00:01:57.900 align:middle line:90%
as a futurist.

00:01:57.900 --> 00:01:59.910 align:middle line:10%
The field of
conscious evolution,

00:01:59.910 --> 00:02:05.130 align:middle line:10%
which has been my study for lo,
these many years, and sometimes

00:02:05.130 --> 00:02:08.698 align:middle line:10%
I say, 13.7 billion years
if they ask how old I am.

00:02:08.698 --> 00:02:09.498 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:02:09.498 --> 00:02:12.486 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:02:12.486 --> 00:02:13.980 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:13.980 --> 00:02:39.880 align:middle line:90%


00:02:39.880 --> 00:02:42.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Are there are any women
over 50 in this room?

00:02:42.300 --> 00:02:43.440 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:02:43.440 --> 00:02:45.460 align:middle line:90%


00:02:45.460 --> 00:02:47.450 align:middle line:10%
>> I have a new word for us--

00:02:47.450 --> 00:02:49.578 align:middle line:10%
it's regenopause.

00:02:49.578 --> 00:02:50.410 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:02:50.410 --> 00:02:51.210 align:middle line:90%


00:02:51.210 --> 00:02:53.680 align:middle line:84%
>> We are definitely
not declining.

00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:56.810 align:middle line:90%
We seem to be more vital.

00:02:56.810 --> 00:03:02.790 align:middle line:84%
And we are shifting from maximum
procreation to co-create.

00:03:02.790 --> 00:03:05.670 align:middle line:84%
If we're not going to be
having maximum number of babies

00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:12.430 align:middle line:84%
and dying young, and we're going
to be living many longer years,

00:03:12.430 --> 00:03:15.540 align:middle line:84%
and having ever fewer children,
and only chosen children,

00:03:15.540 --> 00:03:19.300 align:middle line:84%
at the best, and some
having no children,

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:24.030 align:middle line:84%
the energy that went into the
vast effort of reproducing

00:03:24.030 --> 00:03:31.206 align:middle line:84%
the species is shifting to the
energy of evolving the species,

00:03:31.206 --> 00:03:33.905 align:middle line:90%
and it's as great as sex.

00:03:33.905 --> 00:03:35.180 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:03:35.180 --> 00:03:36.030 align:middle line:90%


00:03:36.030 --> 00:03:37.380 align:middle line:90%
>> We are shifting.

00:03:37.380 --> 00:03:40.620 align:middle line:84%
And what it means to have
a gentle birth rather than

00:03:40.620 --> 00:03:43.140 align:middle line:90%
a disaster catastrophe birth--

00:03:43.140 --> 00:03:45.360 align:middle line:90%
because it's going to change--

00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:48.930 align:middle line:84%
is going to be the degree to
which we connect that which

00:03:48.930 --> 00:03:50.852 align:middle line:90%
is already creative and here.

00:03:50.852 --> 00:03:52.298 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:03:52.298 --> 00:03:53.744 align:middle line:90%


00:03:53.744 --> 00:03:56.250 align:middle line:10%
>> Barbara's quest is to--

00:03:56.250 --> 00:03:59.570 align:middle line:10%
one, it's sort of a
Paul Revere requirement

00:03:59.570 --> 00:04:01.700 align:middle line:10%
to alert everybody
who can possibly

00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:06.320 align:middle line:10%
hear about the coming
necessity for dramatic shift

00:04:06.320 --> 00:04:07.880 align:middle line:10%
in consciousness.

00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:10.850 align:middle line:84%
That's part A. Part
B is to inform people

00:04:10.850 --> 00:04:13.040 align:middle line:84%
what conscious evolution--
what it would look

00:04:13.040 --> 00:04:17.089 align:middle line:84%
like if we consciously chose
to evolve rather than wait

00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:19.339 align:middle line:84%
for biology to take
its time, when there

00:04:19.339 --> 00:04:21.290 align:middle line:90%
is no time for biology to work.

00:04:21.290 --> 00:04:24.590 align:middle line:90%


00:04:24.590 --> 00:04:26.870 align:middle line:84%
>> From what the
scientific evidence is,

00:04:26.870 --> 00:04:30.230 align:middle line:84%
we cannot keep over-growing
in the finite womb and heating

00:04:30.230 --> 00:04:33.020 align:middle line:84%
our climate, and
expect our civilisation

00:04:33.020 --> 00:04:34.460 align:middle line:90%
and our environment to survive.

00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:50.060 align:middle line:90%


00:04:50.060 --> 00:04:53.330 align:middle line:10%
>> Barbara is seen as the
mother of the entire field

00:04:53.330 --> 00:04:54.380 align:middle line:10%
of conscious evolution.

00:04:54.380 --> 00:04:57.182 align:middle line:10%
>> Not just the mother of it,
but the grandmother of it.

00:04:57.182 --> 00:04:59.640 align:middle line:10%
>> You can find that idea going
all the way back a century,

00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:01.250 align:middle line:10%
if not more.

00:05:01.250 --> 00:05:03.870 align:middle line:10%
But something about that
phrase, conscious evolution,

00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:07.460 align:middle line:10%
kind of captured it in a very
simple, understandable way.

00:05:07.460 --> 00:05:25.890 align:middle line:90%


00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:27.890 align:middle line:10%
When Most people think
about the word evolution,

00:05:27.890 --> 00:05:30.110 align:middle line:10%
they think about Darwin
and natural selection

00:05:30.110 --> 00:05:33.290 align:middle line:10%
and random mutation and
neo-darwinism and genetics

00:05:33.290 --> 00:05:36.710 align:middle line:10%
and adaptation, and fitness,
and all of those things.

00:05:36.710 --> 00:05:40.520 align:middle line:84%
But conscious evolution has
more to do with development

00:05:40.520 --> 00:05:42.455 align:middle line:90%
and evolution of human culture.

00:05:42.455 --> 00:05:45.950 align:middle line:84%
And it has to do with the
idea that we can consciously

00:05:45.950 --> 00:05:48.800 align:middle line:84%
shape and make
choices individually

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:51.420 align:middle line:84%
and collectively
that can affect,

00:05:51.420 --> 00:05:53.840 align:middle line:90%
in a positive way, our future.

00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:59.660 align:middle line:10%
>> I think Barbara's message
has always been so rarefied

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:04.520 align:middle line:10%
and progressive that people
who needed a very practical,

00:06:04.520 --> 00:06:09.680 align:middle line:10%
grounded, linear interpretation
of things were not really sure

00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:10.970 align:middle line:10%
what she was really saying.

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:13.490 align:middle line:90%


00:06:13.490 --> 00:06:14.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:06:14.290 --> 00:06:17.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Because Renee was saying,
everybody's talking about

00:06:17.690 --> 00:06:18.490 align:middle line:90%
the vision.

00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:21.660 align:middle line:10%
>> I try and talk about
what my grandmother is up

00:06:21.660 --> 00:06:24.090 align:middle line:10%
to to my friends.

00:06:24.090 --> 00:06:27.060 align:middle line:84%
It's really hard to
present it to them

00:06:27.060 --> 00:06:31.200 align:middle line:84%
in a way that doesn't
sound completely

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:37.910 align:middle line:84%
out there, new wave,
kind of airy-fairyness.

00:06:37.910 --> 00:06:41.140 align:middle line:90%
But is something that's very--

00:06:41.140 --> 00:06:45.370 align:middle line:84%
that's actually
grounded and viable.

00:06:45.370 --> 00:06:50.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Renee, how do you and your
peers feel about the future?

00:06:50.430 --> 00:06:53.260 align:middle line:84%
Is there a sense of the
optimistic, pessimistic,

00:06:53.260 --> 00:06:54.060 align:middle line:90%
concern?

00:06:54.060 --> 00:06:55.790 align:middle line:84%
What's-- if you
could crystallize it?

00:06:55.790 --> 00:06:59.250 align:middle line:84%
>> I would say a resounding
ambivalence, really.

00:06:59.250 --> 00:07:06.030 align:middle line:84%
I have the naive
desire to make my time

00:07:06.030 --> 00:07:08.610 align:middle line:90%
on Earth count for something.

00:07:08.610 --> 00:07:13.225 align:middle line:84%
And so I think our challenge
is to stay true to our heart.

00:07:13.225 --> 00:07:15.425 align:middle line:84%
If I could have
chosen a granddaughter

00:07:15.425 --> 00:07:19.024 align:middle line:84%
to speak that way, that's
what I would have chosen.

00:07:19.024 --> 00:07:19.840 align:middle line:90%
[KISS]

00:07:19.840 --> 00:07:20.796 align:middle line:90%
>> Love you, Granny.

00:07:20.796 --> 00:07:23.760 align:middle line:84%
I was just thinking
how kind of bizarre

00:07:23.760 --> 00:07:27.150 align:middle line:84%
to think that I was
one inside of you

00:07:27.150 --> 00:07:29.840 align:middle line:90%
and you were once inside of you.

00:07:29.840 --> 00:07:43.170 align:middle line:90%


00:07:43.170 --> 00:07:48.900 align:middle line:84%
>> The human species has no
experience of a global crisis

00:07:48.900 --> 00:07:51.138 align:middle line:90%
or opportunity at this scale.

00:07:51.138 --> 00:08:02.730 align:middle line:90%


00:08:02.730 --> 00:08:07.410 align:middle line:10%
Barbara Hubbard is, what I
call, La Madre de La Conciencia.

00:08:07.410 --> 00:08:09.420 align:middle line:10%
And she's actually the
mother of consciousness.

00:08:09.420 --> 00:08:11.800 align:middle line:10%
>> Humanity is at a
kind of crossroads,

00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:14.520 align:middle line:10%
and things are either going
to get worse or they're going

00:08:14.520 --> 00:08:15.602 align:middle line:10%
to get better.

00:08:15.602 --> 00:08:17.310 align:middle line:10%
>> And one of the
things about the shift,

00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:19.601 align:middle line:10%
and one of the things about
being an American visionary

00:08:19.601 --> 00:08:23.100 align:middle line:10%
that Barbara gives us, is the
ability to take a look upstream

00:08:23.100 --> 00:08:24.540 align:middle line:10%
and see how we can be proactive.

00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:26.170 align:middle line:10%
>> And it's not
just little steps.

00:08:26.170 --> 00:08:28.530 align:middle line:10%
It's like really
what's possible.

00:08:28.530 --> 00:08:29.620 align:middle line:10%
It's the transformation.

00:08:29.620 --> 00:08:35.220 align:middle line:10%
>> Transformation can only occur
on this planet when you awaken.

00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:38.716 align:middle line:10%
But as long as you are asleep,
there won't be transformation.

00:08:38.716 --> 00:08:45.860 align:middle line:90%


00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:48.260 align:middle line:90%
The fear is eternal--

00:08:48.260 --> 00:08:51.670 align:middle line:90%
this is my moment in eternity.

00:08:51.670 --> 00:08:55.140 align:middle line:84%
If I lose my chance, I
may have lost it forever.

00:08:55.140 --> 00:09:00.050 align:middle line:90%


00:09:00.050 --> 00:09:02.960 align:middle line:84%
>> There were often times when
she felt like she wasn't being

00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:04.040 align:middle line:90%
effective.

00:09:04.040 --> 00:09:10.520 align:middle line:84%
No, she's referred to herself
as a failure, in some ways.

00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:11.838 align:middle line:90%
>> Surprise.

00:09:11.838 --> 00:09:13.320 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:14.310 align:middle line:90%


00:09:14.310 --> 00:09:15.572 align:middle line:90%
>> How are you?

00:09:15.572 --> 00:09:18.020 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, what do you know?

00:09:18.020 --> 00:09:20.390 align:middle line:90%
Something is happening to me.

00:09:20.390 --> 00:09:23.650 align:middle line:10%
>> There's so much going on,
it's a pretty raucous chorus

00:09:23.650 --> 00:09:24.450 align:middle line:10%
in there.

00:09:24.450 --> 00:09:26.810 align:middle line:10%
There's a lot of rocking
and rolling going on.

00:09:26.810 --> 00:09:28.143 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm talking about?

00:09:28.143 --> 00:09:32.260 align:middle line:84%
>> I do because I have
felt a very unusual fear,

00:09:32.260 --> 00:09:34.280 align:middle line:90%
and it isn't about something.

00:09:34.280 --> 00:09:40.085 align:middle line:84%
It seems very, very deep and
not about a particular incident.

00:09:40.085 --> 00:09:43.855 align:middle line:90%
>> I think it's dread.

00:09:43.855 --> 00:09:47.360 align:middle line:84%
>> I wake up in the morning
sometimes with this clenching

00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:50.570 align:middle line:90%
in my solar plexus of fear.

00:09:50.570 --> 00:09:55.190 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying to get in touch
with exactly what the fear is,

00:09:55.190 --> 00:09:57.050 align:middle line:84%
because it's not
that I think I could

00:09:57.050 --> 00:10:01.520 align:middle line:84%
fail at something that isn't
a natural planetary event.

00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:06.095 align:middle line:84%
But I have a fear
that we won't do it.

00:10:06.095 --> 00:10:11.530 align:middle line:10%
>> And she has this tendency
to feel driven, overwhelmed,

00:10:11.530 --> 00:10:12.410 align:middle line:10%
compulsive.

00:10:12.410 --> 00:10:16.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean, she's got to do her best
and there's not enough time.

00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:22.700 align:middle line:84%
>> I am, by far, more alive and
useful to anyone or anything

00:10:22.700 --> 00:10:25.020 align:middle line:84%
if I'm following
the deepest impulse,

00:10:25.020 --> 00:10:28.410 align:middle line:84%
which is to be a visionary
and to express vision,

00:10:28.410 --> 00:10:31.130 align:middle line:84%
than I am when I'm not at
all good at organizing.

00:10:31.130 --> 00:10:33.920 align:middle line:10%
>> There has to be some
organizational structure

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:37.370 align:middle line:10%
for change and that's
not Barbara's thing.

00:10:37.370 --> 00:10:40.940 align:middle line:84%
And so either that has
to be attracted and then

00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:43.760 align:middle line:84%
really supported by
some kind of person who

00:10:43.760 --> 00:10:48.290 align:middle line:84%
would be willing to run
that, which she's not--

00:10:48.290 --> 00:10:50.498 align:middle line:84%
I haven't seen that
person come forward yet.

00:10:50.498 --> 00:10:51.298 align:middle line:90%
[DOORBELL RINGS]

00:10:51.298 --> 00:10:55.290 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, Stephen!

00:10:55.290 --> 00:10:56.787 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello, Barbara.

00:10:56.787 --> 00:10:57.695 align:middle line:90%
Hi.

00:10:57.695 --> 00:11:03.260 align:middle line:10%
>> Stephen Dinan invited me
to speak on the Shift Network.

00:11:03.260 --> 00:11:06.410 align:middle line:10%
And my program, Agents
of Conscious Evolution,

00:11:06.410 --> 00:11:09.380 align:middle line:10%
invited people to come
together to understand

00:11:09.380 --> 00:11:11.330 align:middle line:10%
the evolutionary story
and work together

00:11:11.330 --> 00:11:13.490 align:middle line:10%
toward a planetary birth.

00:11:13.490 --> 00:11:16.610 align:middle line:10%
>> She's been given
glimpses of the future,

00:11:16.610 --> 00:11:19.430 align:middle line:10%
templates that she's
lived in her own body.

00:11:19.430 --> 00:11:22.050 align:middle line:10%
And sometimes, there are
frustrations that she

00:11:22.050 --> 00:11:24.860 align:middle line:10%
was given these templates
and they hadn't manifested.

00:11:24.860 --> 00:11:27.864 align:middle line:84%
But her time was really
not fully until now.

00:11:27.864 --> 00:11:29.316 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:29.316 --> 00:11:40.470 align:middle line:90%


00:11:40.470 --> 00:11:44.170 align:middle line:10%
>> The Mayans, they add a long
calendar that ends on December

00:11:44.170 --> 00:11:50.620 align:middle line:10%
21st, 2012.

00:11:50.620 --> 00:11:54.310 align:middle line:10%
The media has made it
into a possible doomsday,

00:11:54.310 --> 00:11:56.016 align:middle line:10%
an end of civilization.

00:11:56.016 --> 00:11:57.640 align:middle line:10%
And there's a lot of
attention to that.

00:11:57.640 --> 00:11:58.978 align:middle line:10%
>> [SCREAMS]

00:11:58.978 --> 00:11:59.870 align:middle line:10%


00:11:59.870 --> 00:12:03.740 align:middle line:10%
>> The film "2012" is apparently
scaring people who actually

00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:05.495 align:middle line:10%
think the world may end soon.

00:12:05.495 --> 00:12:09.830 align:middle line:10%
>> So Barbara, realizing that
all this focus and attention

00:12:09.830 --> 00:12:13.211 align:middle line:10%
was being put on this date,
the end of the Mayan calendar.

00:12:13.211 --> 00:12:15.710 align:middle line:84%
So people were really focused
on, what's going to come next?

00:12:15.710 --> 00:12:16.793 align:middle line:90%
What's going to come next?

00:12:16.793 --> 00:12:17.690 align:middle line:90%
Oh my God.

00:12:17.690 --> 00:12:19.460 align:middle line:84%
So she thought,
well, if they're all

00:12:19.460 --> 00:12:21.610 align:middle line:84%
focused on something's
going to shift, something's

00:12:21.610 --> 00:12:23.235 align:middle line:84%
going to change, why
don't we give them

00:12:23.235 --> 00:12:25.280 align:middle line:84%
something really
valuable to embrace

00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:26.450 align:middle line:90%
as what's beyond that date?

00:12:26.450 --> 00:12:27.250 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:27.250 --> 00:12:31.993 align:middle line:10%
>> December 22nd, the
birthday of a new humanity.

00:12:31.993 --> 00:12:35.360 align:middle line:10%
Day one of a new era.

00:12:35.360 --> 00:12:39.260 align:middle line:84%
>> The idea was planted in my
mind that I should be telling

00:12:39.260 --> 00:12:41.495 align:middle line:84%
the story of the Birth
on December 22nd.

00:12:41.495 --> 00:12:45.040 align:middle line:90%


00:12:45.040 --> 00:12:48.846 align:middle line:84%
However, that's done is
still a mystery to me, but--

00:12:48.846 --> 00:12:52.200 align:middle line:84%
(VOICEOVER) And so I partner
with a fellow visionary,

00:12:52.200 --> 00:12:56.650 align:middle line:84%
Stephen Dinan, to plan
a big media event.

00:12:56.650 --> 00:12:59.980 align:middle line:90%
We're calling it Birth 2012.

00:12:59.980 --> 00:13:03.160 align:middle line:84%
We'll host a large
gathering in Los Angeles,

00:13:03.160 --> 00:13:06.205 align:middle line:84%
and people around the globe
will celebrate locally.

00:13:06.205 --> 00:13:08.447 align:middle line:84%
>> --for birthing a whole
planet, you have to--

00:13:08.447 --> 00:13:09.280 align:middle line:90%
>> It's not too bad.

00:13:09.280 --> 00:13:13.150 align:middle line:84%
>> [LAUGHS] The goal of Birth
2012 is to create a unifying

00:13:13.150 --> 00:13:16.270 align:middle line:84%
moment for humanity that marks
the beginning of a new era

00:13:16.270 --> 00:13:18.070 align:middle line:90%
for human possibility.

