life, was my husband, Earl.

00:30:36.470 --> 00:30:40.740 align:middle line:90%


00:30:40.740 --> 00:30:45.450 align:middle line:10%
>> They met in 1949, in
Paris, at a wonderful little

00:30:45.450 --> 00:30:47.230 align:middle line:10%
restaurant on the left bank.

00:30:47.230 --> 00:30:49.200 align:middle line:10%
And it was one of
those setups where

00:30:49.200 --> 00:30:52.440 align:middle line:10%
there were long tables and
people would just sit down

00:30:52.440 --> 00:30:54.000 align:middle line:10%
wherever there was a space.

00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:55.980 align:middle line:84%
>> And at that time,
I was attempting to be

00:30:55.980 --> 00:30:57.960 align:middle line:90%
an existentialist.

00:30:57.960 --> 00:31:02.070 align:middle line:84%
So I had a goulash
cigarette and I ordered

00:31:02.070 --> 00:31:04.560 align:middle line:90%
a half bottle of red wine.

00:31:04.560 --> 00:31:08.820 align:middle line:84%
When this young man came
