changed my life.

00:34:35.360 --> 00:34:41.170 align:middle line:90%


00:34:41.170 --> 00:34:45.900 align:middle line:10%
>> He saw her, that she was
seeing something that was

00:34:45.900 --> 00:34:46.800 align:middle line:10%
different.

00:34:46.800 --> 00:34:50.610 align:middle line:84%
And that she was, in fact,
the cutting edge of evolution.

00:34:50.610 --> 00:34:55.620 align:middle line:84%
And to be seen like that for the
first time rather than neurotic

00:34:55.620 --> 00:35:02.450 align:middle line:84%
and discontent and what's
wrong with you, was revelatory.

00:35:02.450 --> 00:35:06.930 align:middle line:84%
>> But the bigger
revelation was yet to come.

00:35:06.930 --> 00:35:10.350 align:middle line:84%
It was a vision of the
future for all of us.

00:35:10.350 --> 00:35:13.620 align:middle line:90%


00:35:13.620 --> 00:35:17.340 align:middle line:10%
The second major question
that shaped my life

00:35:17.340 --> 00:35:22.350 align:middle line:10%
was what is our story
comparable to the story

00:35:22.350 --> 00:35:23.420 align:middle line:10%
of the birth of Christ?

00:35:23.420 --> 00:35:26.820 align:middle line:90%


00:35:26.820 --> 00:35:29.210 align:middle line:84%
In the gospel, there
was a simple story

00:35:29.210 --> 00:35:32.360 align:middle line:84%
that anybody could
understand-- a child is born

00:35:32.360 --> 00:35:35.390 align:middle line:90%
and then all the rest followed.

00:35:35.390 --> 00:35:37.280 align:middle line:90%
What's our story?

00:35:37.280 --> 00:35:41.300 align:middle line:84%
What's our story that would
be comparable to the story

00:35:41.300 --> 00:35:43.250 align:middle line:90%
