lot of the star power.

00:40:29.430 --> 00:40:33.105 align:middle line:84%
If we're fortunate, there's good
leads with Sting and Santana.

00:40:33.105 --> 00:40:34.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Who's the target audience?

00:40:34.410 --> 00:40:36.390 align:middle line:84%
>> For the leading
edge, New Age,

00:40:36.390 --> 00:40:38.974 align:middle line:84%
new paradigm kind of folks that
will be kind of more attracted

00:40:38.974 --> 00:40:41.306 align:middle line:84%
in at the beginning, those
are the people who tend to be

00:40:41.306 --> 00:40:43.257 align:middle line:84%
activating a lot of
events right now.

00:40:43.257 --> 00:40:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And then it's going to
kind of keep building

00:40:45.090 --> 00:40:47.085 align:middle line:90%
to be more and more mainstream.

00:40:47.085 --> 00:40:49.626 align:middle line:84%
It has to be accessible
to a broad audience

00:40:49.626 --> 00:40:52.000 align:middle line:84%
because I think it's going to
be seen by a lot of people.

00:40:52.000 --> 00:41:05.340 align:middle line:90%


00:41:05.340 --> 00:41:10.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The only answer to stopping
war and stopping destruction is

00:41:10.170 --> 00:41:14.920 align:middle line:84%
connecting up, very rapidly,
that which is creative, loving,

00:41:14.920 --> 00:41:20.160 align:middle line:84%
kind, and showing the shift
that nature and human nature is

00:41:20.160 --> 00:41:23.716 align:middle line:84%
actually doing now, but
hasn't yet become visible.

00:41:23.716 --> 00:41:38.360 align:middle line:90%


00:41:38.360 --> 00:41:43.610 align:middle line:10%
>> The shift is much closer
than most people realize.

00:41:43.610 --> 00:41:45.620 align:middle line:10%
We are already there.

00:41:45.620 --> 00:41:49.550 align:middle line:10%
>> What I'm seeing is this
massive shift worldwide,

00:41:49.550 --> 00:41:53.990 align:middle line:10%
waking up to the fact that
we don't exist in isolation.

00:41:53.990 --> 00:41:57.910 align:middle line:10%
>> A spontaneous
collective awakening,

00:41:57.910 --> 00:41:59.520 align:middle line:10%
and I think that'd
be really exciting.

00:41:59.520 --> 00:42:03.119 align:middle line:10%
>> And that love will be
the currency of exchange.

00:42:03.119 --> 00:42:05.660 align:middle line:10%
And I know it sounds a little
woo-woo and a little out there.

00:42:05.660 --> 00:42:07.240 align:middle line:10%
>> But it is happening.

00:42:07.240 --> 00:42:08.660 align:middle line:10%
When I think
tipping point, is it

00:42:08.660 --> 00:42:10.730 align:middle line:10%
going to be I wake up
tomorrow and it's happened?

00:42:10.730 --> 00:42:11.530 align:middle line:10%
Maybe.

00:42:11.530 --> 00:42:14.840 align:middle line:10%
>> I'm not one who really
buys into the Eureka theory

00:42:14.840 --> 00:42:16.700 align:middle line:10%
of personal transformation.

00:42:16.700 --> 00:42:20.150 align:middle line:10%
I think that change comes
one ah-ha at a time.

00:42:20.150 --> 00:42:21.620 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes, it's one
heart at the time,

00:42:21.620 --> 00:42:23.330 align:middle line:10%
but that can happen very quick.

00:42:23.330 --> 00:42:24.410 align:middle line:10%
That can go viral.

00:42:24.410 --> 00:42:28.850 align:middle line:10%
>> And we also have now is
the ability to reach seven,

00:42:28.850 --> 00:42:31.370 align:middle line:10%
eight billion people
around the world in a week.

00:42:31.370 --> 00:42:36.330 align:middle line:10%
>> And after a while, we reach
a geometric tipping point.

00:42:36.330 --> 00:42:40.380 align:middle line:10%
>> I wouldn't be surprised that
2020 we look back, and we go,

00:42:40.380 --> 00:42:43.885 align:middle line:10%
wow, this is when this
movement started to happen.

00:42:43.885 --> 00:42:47.270 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I'm not sure if we're
going to see a flash point,

00:42:47.270 --> 00:42:49.860 align:middle line:10%
like on a certain date
everyone wakes up and goes, oh,

00:42:49.860 --> 00:42:50.660 align:middle line:10%
I want to hug.

00:42:50.660 --> 00:42:54.188 align:middle line:90%


00:42:54.188 --> 00:42:58.130 align:middle line:84%
>> There's been a tendency
to look for some date,

00:42:58.130 --> 00:43:02.415 align:middle line:84%
some event that is going to
represent a turning point,

00:43:02.415 --> 00:43:05.625 align:middle line:84%
that irrevocable moment when
culture is going to shift.

00:43:05.625 --> 00:43:10.195 align:middle line:10%
>> Our crisis is a birth.

00:43:10.195 --> 00:43:15.980 align:middle line:10%
>> We stand on the precipice of
a dramatic moment of choice--

00:43:15.980 --> 00:43:19.340 align:middle line:10%
extinction or evolution.

00:43:19.340 --> 00:43:23.710 align:middle line:84%
What will it take to turn our
crisis into a historic turning?

00:43:23.710 --> 00:43:26.030 align:middle line:10%
>> There's a romantic
idealism in that,

00:43:26.030 --> 00:43:28.660 align:middle line:10%
and the reverse side of that
is a sort of cynicism when it

00:43:28.660 --> 00:43:30.735 align:middle line:10%
doesn't happen, when
it can't happen.

00:43:30.735 --> 00:43:33.580 align:middle line:84%
>> People have been talking
about the end of the world

00:43:33.580 --> 00:43:35.290 align:middle line:90%
since the world began.

00:43:35.290 --> 00:43:37.662 align:middle line:84%
And often, it's not just
the world collapsing.

00:43:37.662 --> 00:43:38.620 align:middle line:90%
It's not the end times.

00:43:38.620 --> 00:43:44.220 align:middle line:84%
It's something rising out of
it, a new Eden, a new era,

00:43:44.220 --> 00:43:46.410 align:middle line:84%
the dawning of the
Age of Aquarius,

00:43:46.410 --> 00:43:49.170 align:middle line:84%
the rebirth, whatever
you want to call it.

00:43:49.170 --> 00:43:52.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's a powerful force in
the founding of this country.

00:43:52.860 --> 00:43:55.770 align:middle line:10%
I mean, our country was founded
by religious zealots coming

00:43:55.770 --> 00:43:58.890 align:middle line:10%
here, to the new world, thinking
it was the new Jerusalem,

00:43:58.890 --> 00:44:00.150 align:middle line:10%
it was the city on a hill.

00:44:00.150 --> 00:44:02.790 align:middle line:10%
>> And this idea that
we're all going to shift,

00:44:02.790 --> 00:44:04.530 align:middle line:10%
or wake up to a
new consciousness,

00:44:04.530 --> 00:44:09.480 align:middle line:10%
or go through some global
transformation like that, well,

00:44:09.480 --> 00:44:12.100 align:middle line:10%
all kinds of things
may happen over time,

00:44:12.100 --> 00:44:14.670 align:middle line:10%
but there's not going to
be some moment like that.

00:44:14.670 --> 00:44:17.190 align:middle line:84%
And there never could
be and there never

00:44:17.190 --> 00:44:19.470 align:middle line:90%
will be, in my humble opinion.

00:44:19.470 --> 00:44:21.650 align:middle line:10%
>> What is your highest
intention or expectation

00:44:21.650 --> 00:44:22.776 align:middle line:10%
for this event?

00:44:22.776 --> 00:44:23.592 align:middle line:10%
Describe that.

00:44:23.592 --> 00:44:27.600 align:middle line:10%
>> There will be a shift of
consciousness on planet Earth

00:44:27.600 --> 00:44:29.820 align:middle line:10%
during the planetary
birth experience.

00:44:29.820 --> 00:44:32.620 align:middle line:90%


00:44:32.620 --> 00:44:35.380 align:middle line:84%
We've seen it from
space-- we are one planet.

00:44:35.380 --> 00:44:36.597 align:middle line:90%
We are all members of it.

00:44:36.597 --> 00:44:40.080 align:middle line:90%


00:44:40.080 --> 00:44:42.190 align:middle line:10%
All the pioneers of
the peace movement,

00:44:42.190 --> 00:44:44.650 align:middle line:10%
the women's movement, the
civil rights movement,

00:44:44.650 --> 00:44:47.040 align:middle line:10%
the consciousness movement,
the futurist movement,

00:44:47.040 --> 00:44:50.120 align:middle line:10%
all those great movements,
they're toward a new culture.

00:44:50.120 --> 00:44:52.700 align:middle line:90%


00:44:52.700 --> 00:44:55.880 align:middle line:84%
We do have the
capacity, if we connect,

00:44:55.880 --> 00:44:58.460 align:middle line:84%
to meet the basic
needs of humanity,

00:44:58.460 --> 00:45:00.620 align:middle line:90%
stop fighting, and move forward.

00:45:00.620 --> 00:45:05.000 align:middle line:84%
When enough people feel
that simultaneously,

00:45:05.000 --> 00:45:08.960 align:middle line:84%
the consciousness will shift
and the behavior pattern

00:45:08.960 --> 00:45:11.260 align:middle line:84%
of self-centric
consciousness will diminish.

00:45:11.260 --> 00:45:18.680 align:middle line:90%


00:45:18.680 --> 00:45:21.060 align:middle line:90%
The stakes are everything.

00:45:21.060 --> 00:45:23.540 align:middle line:90%
The gamble is absolute.

00:45:23.540 --> 00:45:26.510 align:middle line:90%
The odds are millions to one.

00:45:26.510 --> 00:45:30.858 align:middle line:84%
Yet, I have no choice
but to do my best.

00:45:30.858 --> 00:45:36.980 align:middle line:84%
>> We have main engine starts,
four, three, two, one, zero.

00:45:36.980 --> 00:45:40.445 align:middle line:90%
Lift off.

00:45:40.445 --> 00:45:45.200 align:middle line:84%
>> My husband Earl and I
were focused on the question,

00:45:45.200 --> 00:45:49.580 align:middle line:84%
what new achievements had
the power to literally change

00:45:49.580 --> 00:45:52.850 align:middle line:90%
humanity in a moment?

00:45:52.850 --> 00:45:56.630 align:middle line:84%
It started, actually, with
the American Space Program

00:45:56.630 --> 00:46:00.330 align:middle line:84%
and the Apollo program, and
realizing we were becoming

00:46:00.330 --> 00:46:02.910 align:middle line:90%
extraterrestrials ourselves.

00:46:02.910 --> 00:46:06.530 align:middle line:84%
Then we began to speak
about it and write about it.

00:46:06.530 --> 00:46:10.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Many of the counter-cultura
movements of the 1960s and 70s

00:46:10.550 --> 00:46:13.340 align:middle line:84%
were anti-technology,
or anti-modern,

00:46:13.340 --> 00:46:15.620 align:middle line:90%
or even anti-American.

00:46:15.620 --> 00:46:19.850 align:middle line:84%
But Barbara, she was pro of the
space program, pro-technology.

00:46:19.850 --> 00:46:20.960 align:middle line:90%
She was optimistic.

00:46:20.960 --> 00:46:23.540 align:middle line:84%
She had this kind of
forward-looking vision.

00:46:23.540 --> 00:46:28.440 align:middle line:84%
She didn't want to go back
to a earlier, simpler time.

00:46:28.440 --> 00:46:33.460 align:middle line:84%
That optimism is so
quintessentially American.

00:46:33.460 --> 00:46:35.390 align:middle line:84%
She really kind
of carried forward

00:46:35.390 --> 00:46:37.620 align:middle line:84%
some quality of
her own upbringing

00:46:37.620 --> 00:46:41.690 align:middle line:84%
and of her father's maybe
simplistic and naive, but also

00:46:41.690 --> 00:46:46.100 align:middle line:84%
powerful optimistic vision
of what this country could

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:47.772 align:middle line:90%
be and should be.

00:46:47.772 --> 00:46:51.740 align:middle line:84%
>> We saw it, really, as a
direction for human evolution.

00:46:51.740 --> 00:46:54.680 align:middle line:10%
>> They would go out together
and be talking about this,

00:46:54.680 --> 00:46:58.070 align:middle line:10%
but it used to be my father
mainly talking about it.

00:46:58.070 --> 00:47:03.080 align:middle line:84%
But he didn't have
that radiant quality

00:47:03.080 --> 00:47:06.440 align:middle line:84%
that my mother did,
being pregnant with this.

00:47:06.440 --> 00:47:09.560 align:middle line:84%
And people were
attracted to her,

00:47:09.560 --> 00:47:12.020 align:middle line:90%
and that really hurt my father.

00:47:12.020 --> 00:47:18.700 align:middle line:10%
>> All of a sudden, it became
unbearable not to be able

00:47:18.700 --> 00:47:20.940 align:middle line:10%
to have a stage of her own.

00:47:20.940 --> 00:47:25.360 align:middle line:90%


00:47:25.360 --> 00:47:28.500 align:middle line:84%
>> And the reason I left Earl
is I couldn't express my life

00:47:28.500 --> 00:47:32.250 align:middle line:84%
purpose directly with
him because he saw it

00:47:32.250 --> 00:47:36.760 align:middle line:84%
as a suppression of him,
or a rejection of him,

00:47:36.760 --> 00:47:39.737 align:middle line:84%
even though I thought
of it as an expansion.

00:47:39.737 --> 00:47:44.610 align:middle line:90%


00:47:44.610 --> 00:47:48.600 align:middle line:84%
When I saw the first human
footsteps on the moon,

00:47:48.600 --> 00:47:50.940 align:middle line:90%
I wept with joy.

00:47:50.940 --> 00:47:52.920 align:middle line:90%
We were being born.

00:47:52.920 --> 00:47:57.490 align:middle line:84%
We had breached
the tomb of earth.

00:47:57.490 --> 00:48:01.360 align:middle line:84%
We met with scientists
and astronauts,

00:48:01.360 --> 00:48:04.510 align:middle line:84%
and came up with a
new global goal--

00:48:04.510 --> 00:48:10.060 align:middle line:84%
to use the great technologies
developed in the Apollo program

00:48:10.060 --> 00:48:12.640 align:middle line:84%
to build new worlds
on this Earth,

00:48:12.640 --> 00:48:16.540 align:middle line:90%
as well as new worlds in space.

00:48:16.540 --> 00:48:19.660 align:middle line:84%
Together with my new
partner, John Whiteside,

00:48:19.660 --> 00:48:22.600 align:middle line:84%
we went to NASA to
see how it would

00:48:22.600 --> 00:48:26.320 align:middle line:84%
be possible for the people
to participate in the space

00:48:26.320 --> 00:48:28.130 align:middle line:90%
movement.

00:48:28.130 --> 00:48:31.720 align:middle line:84%
So John Whiteside and I
went to Werner von Braun,

00:48:31.720 --> 00:48:36.400 align:middle line:84%
and we said, we
would like to ask you

00:48:36.400 --> 00:48:38.920 align:middle line:84%
if the people could
rent a Saturn V

00:48:38.920 --> 00:48:41.440 align:middle line:90%
rocket for involvement.

00:48:41.440 --> 00:48:43.250 align:middle line:90%
And he was totally stunned.

00:48:43.250 --> 00:48:44.440 align:middle line:90%
He was amazed.

00:48:44.440 --> 00:48:46.281 align:middle line:90%
At first, he said, what?

00:48:46.281 --> 00:48:48.280 align:middle line:84%
And then finally, he said,
well, I don't see why

00:48:48.280 --> 00:48:51.670 align:middle line:90%
not if you can get $400 million.

00:48:51.670 --> 00:48:54.070 align:middle line:84%
And we had astronauts
that wanted to do it,

00:48:54.070 --> 00:48:58.330 align:middle line:84%
so we were taken in to look
at the Saturn V rocket.

00:48:58.330 --> 00:49:03.790 align:middle line:84%
And I quite remember taking
out of my purse, my lipstick,

00:49:03.790 --> 00:49:07.350 align:middle line:84%
and writing on this
huge Saturn V rocket,

00:49:07.350 --> 00:49:08.740 align:middle line:90%
"the people's rocket."

00:49:08.740 --> 00:49:13.420 align:middle line:90%


00:49:13.420 --> 00:49:16.780 align:middle line:84%
The vision of bringing
the people into space

00:49:16.780 --> 00:49:18.880 align:middle line:90%
almost happened.

00:49:18.880 --> 00:49:24.220 align:middle line:84%
Everyone said yes, except
the administration of NASA.

00:49:24.220 --> 00:49:28.720 align:middle line:84%
I was naive to think the
world could change quickly.

00:49:28.720 --> 00:49:33.340 align:middle line:84%
Simply because I could imagine
it didn't mean others could.

00:49:33.340 --> 00:49:37.090 align:middle line:84%
But I learned to say
yes to the possibility,

00:49:37.090 --> 00:49:41.300 align:middle line:84%
and I saw that big visions open
up other people's sense of what

00:49:41.300 --> 00:49:42.100 align:middle line:90%
is possible.

00:49:42.100 --> 00:49:52.450 align:middle line:90%


00:49:52.450 --> 00:49:56.830 align:middle line:84%
We were going to be able
to intentionally create

00:49:56.830 --> 00:49:59.650 align:middle line:84%
a more positive future,
but we couldn't do it

00:49:59.650 --> 00:50:02.050 align:middle line:90%
if we didn't have visions of it.

00:50:02.050 --> 00:50:04.900 align:middle line:84%
We couldn't do it if we
didn't have images of it.

00:50:04.900 --> 00:50:11.080 align:middle line:90%


00:50:11.080 --> 00:50:16.570 align:middle line:10%
I think that you might find
by 2050 that we have restored

00:50:16.570 --> 00:50:19.390 align:middle line:10%
and have become
sustainable on this Earth,

00:50:19.390 --> 00:50:22.750 align:middle line:10%
that we have moved
into self-governing

00:50:22.750 --> 00:50:24.390 align:middle line:10%
at a global scale.

00:50:24.390 --> 00:50:26.530 align:middle line:84%
As a nation state
and the cultures

00:50:26.530 --> 00:50:31.540 align:middle line:84%
that created them will probably
become cultural artifacts,

00:50:31.540 --> 00:50:35.920 align:middle line:84%
like the monarchy
in Great Britain.

00:50:35.920 --> 00:50:41.530 align:middle line:84%
War will be considered outmoded
and obscene and unnecessary.

00:50:41.530 --> 00:50:46.420 align:middle line:84%
I think we'll have communities
beginning in outer space,

00:50:46.420 --> 00:50:48.400 align:middle line:90%
in the solar system.

00:50:48.400 --> 00:50:52.300 align:middle line:84%
I think we will have developed
solar energy from space, which

00:50:52.300 --> 00:50:55.840 align:middle line:84%
will completely change
the economic system based

00:50:55.840 --> 00:50:57.130 align:middle line:90%
on fossil fuels.

00:50:57.130 --> 00:50:59.500 align:middle line:10%
I believe we will
have really developed

00:50:59.500 --> 00:51:03.280 align:middle line:10%
a monetary democracy
which is alternative forms

00:51:03.280 --> 00:51:06.580 align:middle line:10%
of complementary currencies
so that we're not

00:51:06.580 --> 00:51:10.935 align:middle line:10%
the victims of a monetary system
designed on debt and scarcity.

00:51:10.935 --> 00:51:14.410 align:middle line:90%


00:51:14.410 --> 00:51:18.130 align:middle line:84%
And since we are deeply focused
on understanding and getting

00:51:18.130 --> 00:51:21.850 align:middle line:84%
over these terrible
diseases, like cancer,

00:51:21.850 --> 00:51:27.640 align:middle line:84%
I think that we will have
discovered how to extend life

00:51:27.640 --> 00:51:32.370 align:middle line:84%
and how to improve
the quality of life.

00:51:32.370 --> 00:51:35.640 align:middle line:84%
The greatest blessing
is the freedom

00:51:35.640 --> 00:51:38.440 align:middle line:90%
to do your life purpose.

00:51:38.440 --> 00:51:41.970 align:middle line:84%
And in this society,
people will really

00:51:41.970 --> 00:51:45.600 align:middle line:84%
be yearning to be able to
give their gift and create.

00:51:45.600 --> 00:51:47.820 align:middle line:84%
