01:03:41.770 --> 01:03:44.170 align:middle line:10%
Today, Russian
President Vladimir Putin

01:03:44.170 --> 01:03:45.640 align:middle line:10%
weighed in at a
press conference.

01:03:45.640 --> 01:03:48.004 align:middle line:10%
>> So now they're saying
we have the story we need

01:03:48.004 --> 01:03:50.295 align:middle line:10%
because it's on the front
page of "The New York Times."

01:03:50.295 --> 01:03:52.115 align:middle line:10%
But now they're
calling up the people

01:03:52.115 --> 01:03:55.302 align:middle line:10%
who wrote the article and
the Moscow correspondents

01:03:55.302 --> 01:03:57.226 align:middle line:10%
and what's actually
happening in Russia.

01:03:57.226 --> 01:04:00.170 align:middle line:10%
All of this just as I'm leaving.

01:04:00.170 --> 01:04:04.580 align:middle line:10%
Now for me, since I've
spent at least 50 years

01:04:04.580 --> 01:04:08.540 align:middle line:10%
saying this is the news,
it's very hard for me.

01:04:08.540 --> 01:04:10.915 align:middle line:84%
>> Now but you can still--
they're going to be looking

01:04:10.915 --> 01:04:13.290 align:middle line:90%
for talking heads.

01:04:13.290 --> 01:04:16.140 align:middle line:10%
>> And the thing is, also--

01:04:16.140 --> 01:04:20.580 align:middle line:10%
>> She felt that she wasn't
reaching enough people quickly

01:04:20.580 --> 01:04:23.910 align:middle line:10%
enough, that many of her peers
who absolutely adore her,

01:04:23.910 --> 01:04:25.800 align:middle line:10%
were somehow
becoming more famous,

01:04:25.800 --> 01:04:28.890 align:middle line:10%
were being asked to be on
television shows that she

01:04:28.890 --> 01:04:30.630 align:middle line:10%
hadn't been asked to be on.

01:04:30.630 --> 01:04:31.830 align:middle line:10%
There was a sense--

01:04:31.830 --> 01:04:34.050 align:middle line:10%
I don't ever think it
was for her personal ego,

01:04:34.050 --> 01:04:36.560 align:middle line:10%
but the sense that she was
failing in this mission that

01:04:36.560 --> 01:04:37.560 align:middle line:10%
meant everything to her.

01:04:37.560 --> 01:04:39.440 align:middle line:10%
>> I'm angry.

01:04:39.440 --> 01:04:40.850 align:middle line:10%
>> You're very wide awake.

01:04:40.850 --> 01:04:41.320 align:middle line:10%
>> It's no time to get tired.

01:04:41.320 --> 01:04:41.790 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

01:04:41.790 --> 01:04:42.590 align:middle line:10%
>> [LAUGHS]

01:04:42.590 --> 01:04:43.670 align:middle line:10%
>> I'm angry at this.

01:04:43.670 --> 01:04:47.330 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it was more
than a heartbreak.

01:04:47.330 --> 01:04:53.060 align:middle line:10%
It was like a disruption that
really left kind of her spirit

01:04:53.060 --> 01:04:54.890 align:middle line:10%
fractured.

01:04:54.890 --> 01:04:57.890 align:middle line:84%
That this was the
birth to be announced,

01:04:57.890 --> 01:05:02.010 align:middle line:84%
and it was the particular moment
for the great announcement that

01:05:02.010 --> 01:05:02.810 align:middle line:90%
never happened.

01:05:02.810 --> 01:05:19.830 align:middle line:90%


01:05:19.830 --> 01:05:25.030 align:middle line:84%
>> We have to reframe
what we mean by news.

01:05:25.030 --> 01:05:28.630 align:middle line:84%
Currently, news is an
infantile nervous system

01:05:28.630 --> 01:05:30.970 align:middle line:84%
reporting on disaster
and breakdown

01:05:30.970 --> 01:05:33.690 align:middle line:90%
and putting us to sleep.

01:05:33.690 --> 01:05:37.660 align:middle line:84%
The new news is reporting on
what's emerging, creative,

01:05:37.660 --> 01:05:41.230 align:middle line:84%
and where we want
to go to create it.

01:05:41.230 --> 01:05:42.920 align:middle line:90%
You need both.

01:05:42.920 --> 01:05:44.420 align:middle line:84%
You need to know
it's breaking down,

01:05:44.420 --> 01:05:46.390 align:middle line:84%
but it will kill you
if that's all you know.

01:05:46.390 --> 01:05:59.990 align:middle line:90%


01:05:59.990 --> 01:06:02.090 align:middle line:10%
>> I don't watch television
news much anymore,

01:06:02.090 --> 01:06:03.870 align:middle line:10%
and I used to own
five TV stations.

01:06:03.870 --> 01:06:08.410 align:middle line:10%
>> The negative news media feeds
the general fear and hysteria

01:06:08.410 --> 01:06:09.210 align:middle line:10%
of the time.

01:06:09.210 --> 01:06:13.310 align:middle line:10%
>> It's been so driven by money
and interests that are not

01:06:13.310 --> 01:06:14.270 align:middle line:10%
coming from the heart.

01:06:14.270 --> 01:06:16.800 align:middle line:10%
>> There needs to be much
more of a solutions-focus.

01:06:16.800 --> 01:06:20.180 align:middle line:10%
>> There's always positive
things going on in the world

01:06:20.180 --> 01:06:22.640 align:middle line:10%
at the same time that
there is negativity.

01:06:22.640 --> 01:06:26.660 align:middle line:84%
>> And there's a lot of reasons
why any of us could fall

01:06:26.660 --> 01:06:27.680 align:middle line:90%
into pessimism.

01:06:27.680 --> 01:06:33.230 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of reasons, on
the other side as well, there's

01:06:33.230 --> 01:06:35.570 align:middle line:84%
a lot of things that are
better than they've ever

01:06:35.570 --> 01:06:38.500 align:middle line:84%
been in human history,
by dramatic margins.

01:06:38.500 --> 01:06:40.925 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the pessimists
kind of ignore all that data.

01:06:40.925 --> 01:06:43.383 align:middle line:10%
>> And as someone who worked
on a newspaper for many years,

01:06:43.383 --> 01:06:44.210 align:middle line:10%
I understand that.

01:06:44.210 --> 01:06:47.210 align:middle line:90%


01:06:47.210 --> 01:06:49.850 align:middle line:84%
The fact is that conflict
and drama make a good story,

01:06:49.850 --> 01:06:53.120 align:middle line:84%
so we tend to focus on
those kinds of stories.

01:06:53.120 --> 01:06:56.174 align:middle line:84%
But there's a lot of
positive social change

01:06:56.174 --> 01:06:57.590 align:middle line:84%
out there that
doesn't get covered

01:06:57.590 --> 01:06:59.545 align:middle line:84%
and that no one's really
paying attention to.

01:06:59.545 --> 01:07:03.230 align:middle line:10%
>> I think she sees Birth
2012 as a way of us showing

01:07:03.230 --> 01:07:07.100 align:middle line:10%
ourselves to ourselves so
that we'll stop believing all

01:07:07.100 --> 01:07:10.370 align:middle line:10%
the negativity and all the
lack that we see in what is now

01:07:10.370 --> 01:07:13.640 align:middle line:10%
our mainstream media, and get
a sense that we're hitting

01:07:13.640 --> 01:07:17.210 align:middle line:10%
the surface with a new story.

01:07:17.210 --> 01:07:20.090 align:middle line:10%
>> Looking at it now, I don't
think we've hit our goal of 100

01:07:20.090 --> 01:07:20.890 align:middle line:10%
million.

01:07:20.890 --> 01:07:23.690 align:middle line:10%
But I think we got to really
accelerate to get to that.

01:07:23.690 --> 01:07:24.835 align:middle line:10%
>> Where are we at now?

01:07:24.835 --> 01:07:26.780 align:middle line:10%
>> I would estimate--

01:07:26.780 --> 01:07:30.390 align:middle line:10%
I don't know, just off the top,
speculating-- five million,

01:07:30.390 --> 01:07:31.415 align:middle line:10%
10 million?

01:07:31.415 --> 01:07:31.850 align:middle line:10%
Yeah.

01:07:31.850 --> 01:07:33.510 align:middle line:10%
>>There are five or 10
million people registered?

01:07:33.510 --> 01:07:35.750 align:middle line:84%
>> No, that that know about
this, heard about this,

01:07:35.750 --> 01:07:37.970 align:middle line:84%
seen it, read-- because
we get a lot of press.

01:07:37.970 --> 01:07:40.850 align:middle line:84%
>> So there's probably at least
40 events that we're going

01:07:40.850 --> 01:07:44.780 align:middle line:84%
to carry feeds from over
the course of the two days,

01:07:44.780 --> 01:07:48.694 align:middle line:84%
so that creates a lot
of technical complexity.

01:07:48.694 --> 01:07:49.860 align:middle line:90%
We're like three weeks away.

01:07:49.860 --> 01:07:51.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how do you
keep yourself going?

01:07:51.990 --> 01:07:54.750 align:middle line:84%
>> I made a commitment to do
an hour of meditation every day

01:07:54.750 --> 01:07:57.003 align:middle line:84%
from now until the
birth, regardless.

01:07:57.003 --> 01:08:13.720 align:middle line:90%


01:08:13.720 --> 01:08:15.800 align:middle line:10%
>> Everyone is excited.

01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:18.010 align:middle line:10%
But beyond the
anticipation, it's

01:08:18.010 --> 01:08:23.229 align:middle line:10%
important for me and for all of
us to visualize our intention.

01:08:23.229 --> 01:08:25.810 align:middle line:84%
We will reach 100
million people.

01:08:25.810 --> 01:08:30.180 align:middle line:84%
We will give birth to
a new era of evolution.

01:08:30.180 --> 01:08:32.713 align:middle line:10%
>> This is really a
fulfillment of a lifetime path.

01:08:32.713 --> 01:08:33.513 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

01:08:33.513 --> 01:08:36.952 align:middle line:10%
>> Faithful to this, almost
15 years you've been faithful

01:08:36.952 --> 01:08:40.796 align:middle line:10%
to this vision and it's come
to fruition at this point.

01:08:40.796 --> 01:08:43.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, this has all come out
of your vision, originally,

01:08:43.430 --> 01:08:44.560 align:middle line:90%
Barbara.

