Many of them were
disillusioned as well.

01:12:46.565 --> 01:12:51.650 align:middle line:10%
And I was receiving calls from
people wanting to know well,

01:12:51.650 --> 01:12:53.330 align:middle line:10%
why had we done all of this?

01:12:53.330 --> 01:12:56.600 align:middle line:84%
>> It was naive and grandiose
to think that that event would

01:12:56.600 --> 01:13:01.760 align:middle line:84%
change the world with the
resources that we had there

01:13:01.760 --> 01:13:02.900 align:middle line:90%
with it.

01:13:02.900 --> 01:13:06.110 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think
it's naive to think

01:13:06.110 --> 01:13:07.580 align:middle line:90%
that the world will change.

01:13:07.580 --> 01:13:10.130 align:middle line:10%
>> I mean, we can't create
it unless we sit down around

01:13:10.130 --> 01:13:13.460 align:middle line:10%
the table and at our computers
